          "capability": "file_read",
          "title": "Filesystem read",
          "severity": "MEDIUM",
          "default_classification": "ask",
          "basis": "declared",
          "confidence": "medium",
          "evidence": {
            "zone": "description",
            "matched": "file content",
            "pattern": "\\b(read[\\s_-]?file|get[\\s_-]?file|file[\\s_-]?contents?|read[\\s_-]?text)\\b",
            "snippet": "\"Images\") Raw base64-encoded file content (no data URL prefix) Filename"
          },
          "rationale": "Reading file contents is the most common SOURCE half of an exfiltration chain \u2014 pair it with any network_egress tool and the server can read a secret/config/document and send it out. Modelling read as a capability is what lets the read-then-send toxic combination fire.",
          "suppressed": false
        },
